13/01/2011
TIRANA, Albania -- Authorities on Wednesday (January 12th) extradited an Italian mafia boss, wanted for drug trafficking and extortion in his country. Albino Prudentino is a suspected leader of the Sacra Corona Unita organised crime group. Arrested in the southern town of Vlora in September, Prudentino's assets in Albania have been seized. The Sacra Corona Unita (Sacred United Crown) is based in the southern Italian region of Apulia and is allied with Eastern European gangs. (Balkan Web, News 24, Top News, Ora News - 12/01/11)
